Clause Text:
Services

{service_provider_designation} shall provide to {customer_identifier} the services (the “Services”) set out in the statement of work, which is attached hereto as Exhibit A (the “Statement of Work”). The Statement of Work shall not be modified or expanded except by written agreement of the Parties.
Clause Help: The agreement needs to include a section that lays out the work you'll perform for your client. Sometimes, it's easier to do that in a statement of work rather than in the body of the agreement itself. That's what you've chosen. Make sure you attach a detailed statement of work to the agreement.
Delete Warning: Your contract should always include a clause setting out what work you'll provide for your customers. Removing this section would defeat the purpose of the agreement.

Clause Text:
Services

{service_provider_designation} shall develop up to {pages_developed} pages on {customer_identifier}’s website, including providing the following services (the “Services”):
Clause Help: This is the section that lays out the services you will provide to your clients. Review the list to make sure it is correct.

Clause Text: Design Services - {service_provider_designation} shall provide design services, which will include {design_services_description}. {customer_identifier} shall be entitled to request up to {revision_limit} revisions of the designs created by {service_provider_designation}. Upon payment of all fees and expenses set forth herein, the {service_provider_designation} shall deliver the designs to the {customer_identifier} as one or more files formatted as {design_file_format} file(s) (the “Design Files”). These files shall be formatted so that individual graphic elements can be downloaded individually.
Clause Help: This section provides that you will include web design services as part of your work for the client.
Delete Warning: If you will provide web design services for your client as part of this agreement, you should include a clause setting that out. In other words, if you delete this clause, make sure to add one setting out the web design services that are included.

Clause Text: Design Services - {service_provider_designation} shall provide design services, which will include {design_services_description}. {customer_identifier} shall be entitled to request up to {revision_limit} revisions of the designs created by {service_provider_designation}.

Clause Text: Website Creation Using A Builder - {service_provider_designation} shall create an interactive website matching the visual design using the {website_builder} page builder. {service_provider_designation} shall write any necessary HTML, CSS, and JavaScript code to supplement the functionality of the builder. While {service_provider_designation} will use current best practices for website development, {service_provider_designation} cannot guarantee that the website will function on all browsers or all versions of all browsers.

Clause Text: Mobile Responsive Design & Development - {service_provider_designation} shall create a mobile responsive version of all pages.
Clause Help: This section explains that you will create mobile responsive versions of the pages. While this is pretty standard these days, it is worth including.
Delete Warning: You said you would provide this service. Have you changed your mind? If you will provide responsive design, you should have a clause saying so.

Clause Text: E-Commerce Store - {service_provider_designation} shall set up and customize an online store, payment gateway, and shopping cart for {customer_identifier} using {ecomm_provider}. This shall include creating up to {product_count} products in the store.
Clause Help: This section provides that you will set up your Client's e-commerce store and sets a limit on the number of products you will set up. That limit is important so you don't end up having to create an unreasonable number of products based on what you are charging your client.
Delete Warning: If you are setting up an e-commerce store for your client, you need to include a provision saying as much. Importantly, you need to include something that limits how many products you will set up. We've built that into this clause.

Clause Text: Accessibility - {service_provider_designation} shall build the site consistent with the industry best practices to make the website accessible under the Americans with Disabilities Act (the “ADA”). The {customer_identifier} recognizes that {service_provider_designation} is not an attorney and the {customer_identifier} is ultimately responsible for ensuring compliance with the ADA.
Clause Help: This sets out that you will work with your client to create a website that is accessible in compliance with the ADA. At the same time, it sets out that you are not an attorney and makes clear that your client is ultimately responsible for ensuring compliance.
Delete Warning: If you are committing to create an accessible website, it is important to set that out in your agreement. Just as importantly, you want to make clear that you are not a lawyer, so your client is ultimately responsible for the legalities.

Clause Text: Search Engine Optimization Set Up - {service_provider_designation} shall set up basic search engine optimization (“SEO”) functionality and will include title tags, meta descriptions, and other basic SEO features on each page of the website.
Clause Help: This sets out that you will provide basic SEO set up for your client's website.
Delete Warning: If you are committing to provide SEO set up services, you should include a clause saying so. If you remove this clause, you should replace it with one that serves the same purpose.

Clause Text: Pixel & Tracking Set Up - {service_provider_designation} will install all necessary pixels and tracking codes on the website.
Clause Help: This sets out that you will set up tracking pixels on your client's website.
Delete Warning: If you are committing to set up tracking pixels for your customer, you should include a clause saying so. If you remove this clause, you should replace it with one that serves the same purpose.

Clause Text:
Excluded Services

{service_provider_designation}’s services under this Agreement do not include domain name registration, web hosting, licenses for plugins, licenses for themes, licenses for fonts, licenses for paid stock photos, or ongoing website maintenance. {service_provider_designation} also will not provide written copy for the pages of the website. {customer_identifier} is responsible for providing all necessary assets required to complete the work, including copy, at the outset of the engagement.
Clause Help: This section makes clear that you will not serve as your client's web host or copywriter.
Delete Warning: Although setting out the services that are not included is not required, it is a good idea to address things that customers might think are included in your services but which are not included. We created this clause with web developers in mind.

Clause Text: Membership/Course Area Set Up - {service_provider_designation} shall set up and customize an online membership or course system for the {customer_identifier} using {membership_tech}. This shall include creating up to {membership_setup_limit} membership areas.
Clause Help: This section explains that you'll set up members-only areas for your client. This would include either a membership or a course. It also has a provision limiting how many different membership areas you'll create.
Delete Warning: If you are committing to set up a membership site element for your client, you should have something in your agreement saying so. If you remove this clause, you should replace it with another clause that serves the same purpose.

Clause Text: Blog Set Up - {service_provider_designation} shall create a blog for the website, including creating a blog landing page and creating an individual blog page template.
Clause Help: This section explains that you'll set up a blog for your clients.
Delete Warning: If you are going to set up a blog within the website, you should make that clear in the agreement. If you remove this clause, you should replace it with another one that serves the same purpose.

Clause Text: Integration With Email Tool - {service_provider_designation} will set up basic integrations with {customer_identifier}’s email service provider, {email_service_provider}. As part of this setup, {service_provider_designation} will create opt-in forms to be used on the website for up to {email_form_limit} different forms in {customer_identifier}’s email service provider.
Clause Help: This sets out that you will help your client integrate their email service and sets a limit on how many forms you'll integrate for them.
Delete Warning: If you are committing to set up an email integration for your customer, you should include a clause saying so and should set a limit. If you remove this clause, you should replace it with one that serves the same purpose.

Clause Text: Support After Launch - {service_provider_designation} shall provide {post_launch_support_length} days of minor updates after the launch of the website. This shall be limited to making updates to fix errors discovered after launch and shall not include work that would constitute a change in design or functionality.
Clause Help: This sets out that you will help your client with minor fixes and updates after the website is launched. It sets a time limit and makes clear this is intended to fix issues that surface after launch, not for redesigns.
Delete Warning: If you are committing to support your client after the website is live, you should include a clause saying so. If you remove this clause, you should replace it with one that serves the same purpose.

Coach shall provide {coaching_calls_per_month} coaching sessions per month to Client. Each coaching session will last {coaching_call_length} minutes and will be conducted {coaching_call_method}.

Clause Text:
Coaching Sessions

The Parties will engage in coaching sessions as purchased by Client that will last {coaching_call_length} minutes and will be conducted {coaching_call_method}. Client shall be responsible for scheduling these coaching sessions at mutually agreeable times at the time of purchasing the session. In exchange for this call, the Client shall make the payment set forth on the checkout page at the time of purchase.

Clause Text:
Availability Between Coaching Sessions

The Parties intend for the Coaching Sessions to be the primary avenue for the Coach to serve the Client but recognize that issues will sometimes arise between those Coaching Sessions. Client shall be entitled to seek guidance from Coach between coaching sessions via {coaching_access_medium}. Coach commits to respond to these coaching requests within {response_time}. Client agrees that Coach's availability between coaching sessions is subject to discretion and can be revoked if, in the Coach's sole discretion, Client is making an unreasonable number of requests between coaching sessions. Before revoking access between coaching sessions, Coach will bring the excessive use to the Client's attention at least once.
Clause Help: This clause explains how the Client will be able to receive coaching between coaching sessions. It sets out that the client will not make excessive use of this availability and gives the Coach the ability to revoke this access if it is being overused.
Delete Warning: If you provide access between coaching sessions, you should have a clause that says so. Just as importantly, you need to set some limits so clients do not abuse this access.

Clause Text:
Services

The Company hereby engages You, and You hereby accept such engagement, as an independent contractor to provide certain services to the Company on the terms and conditions set forth in this Agreement. You shall provide to the Company the services set forth in the statement of work, which is attached hereto as Exhibit A (the “Services”). The Company shall not control the manner or means by which You perform the Services. You shall furnish, at Your own expense, the equipment, supplies, and other materials used to perform the Services.
Clause Help: Your agreement needs to include a section that lays out the work the contractor will perform for the client. To make this agreement versatile, we've set it up for the contractor to create a statement of work that outlines the exact work to be done in detail and to attach that to the agreement.
Delete Warning: Your contract should always include a clause setting out what work a contractor will provide to you. If you do not include a section outlining the services to be provided, you may find yourself in a dispute about whether the contractor has delivered. Removing this section would defeat the purpose of the agreement.

Clause Text:
Training Created Specifically For The Program

{guest_expert_identifier} agrees to create a training entitled {guest_custom_training_name} (the “Custom Training”) specifically for inclusion in the Program. {guest_expert_identifier} specifically agrees to assign and hereby does assign all rights, title, and interest in the Custom Training to the Company. As a result of this assignment, Company shall be the exclusive owner of all rights, including copyright, in the Custom Training. As a condition of receiving this assignment, the Company agrees not to sell the Custom Training individually or include the Custom Training in any program other than the Program, whether paid or free. Further, the Company agrees not to make any derivative works based on the Custom Training.

{guest_expert_identifier} represents and warrants to the Company that the Company will receive good and valid title to the Custom Training, free and clear of all encumbrances and liens of any kind and that the Custom Training is {guest_expert_identifier}'s original work (except for material in the public domain or provided by the Company) and does not and will not violate or infringe upon the intellectual property right or any other right whatsoever of any person, firm, corporation, or other entity.
Clause Help: This clause requires the guest to create a custom training for your program and transfers ownership of that training to your company. It limits your use of the training, saying you'll use it only in the program identified in the preamble. The second paragraph provides an assurance from the guest expert that your use of the training won't constitute copyright infringement.
Delete Warning: You should not remove this clause. Setting out what the guest expert has agreed to provide for your program is a key element of the agreement. If you remove this clause, the guest expert will not have to create a custom training for you and you will not necessarily own any training the guest expert does create.

Clause Text:
Inclusion of Pre-Existing Work

{guest_expert_identifier} hereby agrees to allow the Company to include pre-existing material, including {guest_existing_material_name} (the “Pre-Existing Material”) in the Program. {guest_expert_identifier} grants the Company, its affiliates, successors, and assigns (“Authorized Persons”) a non-exclusive, perpetual, irrevocable, unrestricted, royalty-free license to include the Pre-Existing Material in the Program. As a condition of receiving this license, the Company agrees not to sell the Pre-Existing Material individually or include the Pre-Existing Material in any program other than the Program, whether paid or free. Further, the Company agrees not to make any derivative works based on the Pre-Existing Material. The {guest_expert_identifier} retains all right, title, and interest in and to the Pre-Existing Material without limitation. This agreement does not convey to the Company any right, title, or interest in the Pre-Existing Material, nor a portion thereof, but only constitutes a license to use the Pre-Existing material as specified herein.

{guest_expert_identifier} represents and warrants to the Company that the Company will receive good and valid right to use the Pre-Existing Material, free and clear of all encumbrances and liens of any kind and that the Pre-Existing Material are and shall be {guest_expert_identifier}'s original work (except for material in the public domain or provided by the Company) and does not and will not violate or infringe upon the intellectual property right or any other right whatsoever of any person, firm, corporation, or other entity.
Clause Help: This clause explains that the guest has agreed to let you include one of the guest's existing trainings in your program and gives you the necessary "license" to use it. It limits your use of the training, saying you'll use it only in the program identified in the preamble. The second paragraph provides an assurance from the guest expert that your use of the training won't constitute copyright infringement.
Delete Warning: You should not remove this clause. Setting out what the guest expert has agreed to provide for your program is a key element of the agreement. If you remove this clause, the guest expert will not have to provide existing trainings for you to include in the program and you will not be able to document that you have the right permission to include any training the guest expert does provide.

Clause Text:
Live Training

{guest_expert_identifier} agrees to conduct a live training for Program participants (the “Live Training”). The Live Training will include both a teaching component and a question and answer session. {guest_expert_identifier} shall retain all rights, title, and interest in the underlying material presented during the Live Training and grants the Company its affiliates, successors, and assigns (“Authorized Persons”) a non-exclusive, perpetual, irrevocable, unrestricted, royalty-free license to include that material in the Program. While {guest_expert_identifier} retains title to the underlying material, {guest_expert_identifier} specifically agrees to assign and hereby does assign all rights, title, and interest in the recording of the Live Training to the Company. As a result of this assignment, Company shall be the exclusive owner of all rights, including copyright, in the recording of the Live Training.

As a condition of the rights granted hereunder, the Company agrees not to sell the Live Training individually or include the Live Training in any program other than the Program, whether paid or free. Further, the Company agrees not to make any derivative works based on the Live Training.

{guest_expert_identifier} represents and warrants to the Company that the Company will receive good and valid right to use the recording of the Live Training, free and clear of all encumbrances and liens of any kind and that the material presented during the Live Training are and shall be {guest_expert_identifier}'s original work (except for material in the public domain or provided by the Company) and does not and will not violate or infringe upon the intellectual property right or any other right whatsoever of any person, firm, corporation, or other entity.
Clause Help: This clause explains that the guest has agreed to run a live training for your audience. It provides that the guest will continue to own the underlying material, while your company will own the recording of the live training itself. It limits your use of the training, saying you'll use it only in the program identified in the preamble. The final paragraph provides an assurance from the guest expert that your use of the training won't constitute copyright infringement.
Delete Warning: You should not remove this clause. Setting out what the guest expert has agreed to provide for your program is a key element of the agreement. If you remove this clause, the guest expert will not have to provide the live training. More importantly, assuming the guest provides the training, it will not be clear who owns what.
